{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-1072"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Sugar Manufacturing Coordination"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "1072"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :food/sugar-manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:food-security :food-safety :fair-labor]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :sugarops-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies [:optimization :telemetry]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "SugarOpsAdvisor ⊣ Sugar Governor, a REAL compiled `kotoba-lang/
 langgraph` StateGraph (`sugarops.operation/build`:
 `:intake -> :advise -> :govern -> :decide -+-> :commit /
 :request-approval -> :commit / :hold`), append-only audit ledger
 (`sugarops.store/ledger` + `append-ledger!`, `MemStore` and a
 `DatomicStore` backed by `langchain.db` via `langchain-store.core`).
 Replaces a previously deferred actor: `deps.edn` had an empty
 top-level `:deps {}` with langgraph only reachable via `:dev`
 override-deps (nothing to override); `sugarops.advisor` was a pure
 docstring with no `defprotocol`/implementation at all (a skeleton,
 not a stub); `sugarops.operation` had no `build`, only the pure
 `run-operation`, which took a bare PROPOSAL as a function argument
 rather than ever obtaining one from an Advisor; no audit ledger
 existed anywhere in the repo (`store/append-fact` was dead code,
 only called from tests). Now: `sugarops.advisor` has a real
 `Advisor` protocol + `MockAdvisor` genuinely called from the
 compiled graph's `:advise` node; `sugarops.store` gained a `Store`
 protocol + `MemStore` + `DatomicStore` (proven ≡ by a new
 store-contract test) LAYERED ON TOP OF the original pure-map
 functions (`production-batch`/`batch-already-processed?`/`batch-
 shipment-finalized?` made polymorphic so `sugarops.governor`'s 18
 hard-violation checks work unchanged against either a plain map or a
 live Store); `interrupt-before #{:request-approval}` + an in-memory
 checkpointer give escalated proposals a GENUINE human-in-the-loop
 pause/resume; BOTH `:commit` and `:hold` durably append to the real
 ledger, and `:commit` also applies the real batch-lifecycle side
 effect (`store/log-batch!`/`finalize-shipment!`). Four ops
 (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-food-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only; 18 HARD invariants (op-not-allowed,
 effect-not-propose, batch-not-registered, no-spec-basis,
 evidence-incomplete, moisture/polarization/color/ash/SO2/granulation
 out-of-spec, foreign-material-detected, metal-detector-calibration-
 overdue, weight-variance-excessive, sulfite-label-mismatch,
 sanitation-score-insufficient, food-safety-flag-unresolved,
 already-processed, already-shipment-finalized) plus three
 always-escalate high-stakes ops (`:log-production-batch`/
 `:coordinate-shipment`/`:flag-food-safety-concern`) elaborate this
 blueprint's Governor -- proven end-to-end through the REAL compiled
 graph by a new `test/sugarops/build_test.cljc` (commit / hard-hold /
 escalate-approve-and-mark-processed / escalate-reject-holds) plus a
 `clojure -M:dev:run` demo runner producing 4 distinct real ledger
 entries. 62 tests / 230 assertions green (`clojure -M:dev:test`,
 ALL pre-existing tests still pass unchanged), clj-kondo 0 errors / 0
 warnings."}
